    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Frank Rich's interpretation of "The Bridges of Madison County" is that of a typical, old-fashioned male -- the guy scored (Endpaper/Public Stages: "One-Week Stand," July 25). The appeal of Robert James Waller's book is that the couple connected as soul mates -- something very rare today. People cry at the end because they relate it to their own losses and lack of connection, love and intimacy. ARLYNN GREENBAUM New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
